abstract: The last remaining customer for the cargo version of the Airbus A380 superjumbo jet said it was cancelling its order for 10 planes.
snippet: The last remaining customer for the cargo version of the Airbus A380 superjumbo jet said it was cancelling its order for 10 planes.
lead_paragraph: PARIS, March 2 — United Parcel Service, the last remaining customer for the cargo version of the Airbus A380 superjumbo jet, said on Friday that it was walking away from its order for 10 planes, citing concerns that Airbus would not be able to meet a revised delivery schedule.

headline.main: U.P.S. Walks Away From A380 Order
headline.print_headline: U.P.S. Cancels Plane Order With Airbus
